{
  "stem": "8892.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father, I think that was the biggest argument in my life that I witnessed between my father, my brother, and my mother crying, that she says you go, you go back to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You go on your station, because-- he shook him, and I think even wanted to slap him, but he was six feet tall already.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he says you go, because you are the one who's going make it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You are the one who's going to stay alive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "If you don't go, I go right now to the station house and report you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my oldest brother was very devoted to my mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I knew this.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He just did not want to go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He wanted to go with us to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We didn't know it's called the ghetto, but this is where we are going, and we were going.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this is Sunday afternoon.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We are going with the wagon, and my brother is still home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He stays in the house, and they let you take-- they told you-- my mother even cleaned the kitchen, I remember, before we went into the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my brother stays in the house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They tell you not to lock the doors, but you must take care of your pets.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The dogs, cats-- any Jewish dogs, cats from families have to be killed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, we had a dog, and he was so marvelous and my father's right hand, going with him, following the wagon every time to the slaughterhouse, where my father would put-- go into the summer kitchen we had, where all his boots were and pants, you know, the certain clothes he wore there-- and bloody.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When that dog would smell it and know it that my father is changing, he would just run around.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
